contents.contents: Header name must be a non-empty string.

declarations.comments:
A helper class for defining header names at compile time.

```purescript
contentType :: HeaderName
contentType = staticHeaderName (Proxy :: Proxy "Content-Type")
```
declarations.title: MakeHeaderName

declarations.comments: An HTTP request method.
declarations.title: Method

declarations.comments:
Returns whether an HTTP request with the indicated method always supports
a payload.

The following methods always support payloads:
- `PUT`
- `POST`
- `DELETE`
- `PATCH`

The following methods do **not** always support payloads:
- `GET`
- `HEAD`
- `CONNECT`
- `TRACE`
- `OPTIONS`
declarations.title: alwaysSupportsPayload
